Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific relationship between a specific Bank (= party acting as a supplier of banking services) and one or more other involved parties acting as (potential) consumers of banking services as agreed in one or more banking product or service offerings and/or agreements.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
The study of the activities performed by customers.
The study of customer and all its activities associated with the purchase, use and disposal of goods and services, including the customer's emotional, mental and behavioural responses that precede or follow these activities.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: An (structured) interaction between a customer and a financial institution.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific role of a specific Party in the specific Customer Relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
A dispute related to the customer.
Customer cases are issues that typically require corrective response to some financial transaction.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Rating of the Customer or Customer Relationship for value, credit, risk and etc.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: An agreement between a bank and its customer for a sold product.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The product/service profile for a specific customer or customer relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A stage of a customer relationship, such as lead, prospect, and full-blown customer.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
An offer of an agreement to a prospect.
Notes: The receipt of an offer changes the classification of a party's role from a prospect to a customer. A customer offer is related to a stage in the lifecycle of an agreement with a customer, in which the agreement has been offered to the customer but is not finalised.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Phase in a customer relationship in which a party has been identified as a possible target for a sale.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The use of a product by a customer (in a specific customer relationship) over a specified time period.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific role of a specific Party in the specific relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
A relationship between two or more parties; the parties involved are specified in terms of the roles they play in the relationship.
A Party Relationship is a connection between an instance of a Party and two or more instances of associated objects in the relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Specifies a series of stages that characterize the course of existence of a party relationship in a specific context.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Contact person for a customer in a relationship with a financial institution.

Column.value: The interpreted result of the contact (e.g. completed, customer terminated, timed-out)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The reason and or purpose for the contact (e.g. review, issue, product sales, advice, customer enquiry)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Indicates whether this is an inbound or outbound contact (inbound is customer initiated, outbound is servicing resource initiated).
